    <note>Ma(2) Yuan [3671] Giles, pp. 572-3; Renming Da cidian, p. 868. A daughter has a funerary inscription (See Yang Jialuo 35-106) and another daughter was empress of Liu(2) Zhang (Mingdi, second emperor of the Eastern Han). See biography, and notes, in HouHan shu jijie, 24.1a for details on immediate ancestry, which cites alternative and conflicting sources. The HouHan shu loses a generation and says that his father and grandfather did not hold office because of the rebellion of his great great granduncle, Heluo [20675], whereas other sources note offices for both his father and great grandfather, and none for his grandfather, Chang [24660].</note>
